WEBVTT

00:05.255 --> 00:07.246
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

00:11.011 --> 00:13.798
It's true love when you ﬁght off
caffeine-pumped preppies...

00:13.972 --> 00:16.008
...to get a girl her favorite treat.

00:16.600 --> 00:19.182
I scored you
the last melted mocha mufﬁn.

00:19.353 --> 00:23.767
And I know my inner chocoholic
will never speak to me again...

00:24.108 --> 00:25.598
...but I think I'll pass.

00:25.776 --> 00:29.268
Uh-oh. Something's deﬁnitely up
and it's worse than I thought.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.697
Since the sugar ﬁx didn't do the trick...

00:34.410 --> 00:36.776
...maybe these will turn your frown
upside down.

00:36.954 --> 00:38.239
Jimmy. Oh.

00:38.414 --> 00:42.623
Oh, my God, you must've broken
a whole pen of piggy banks to afford these.

00:42.918 --> 00:46.911
And you are worth every dime,
nickel and penny.

00:48.298 --> 00:52.132
A night on the town, the two of us,
it might be exactly what the doctor ordered.

00:52.302 --> 00:53.758
WOMAN:
Do you have any honey?

00:53.929 --> 00:55.965
MAN:
Sure, here you go.

00:58.809 --> 01:01.141
You're doing that distant thing.

01:05.441 --> 01:08.433
I'm sorry, I think an old friend
just buzzed into town.

01:08.610 --> 01:10.271
Wait here.

01:11.905 --> 01:13.236
[SIGHS]

01:14.158 --> 01:17.742
MAN [OVER PHONE]: Belle Reve Hospital.
-Yeah. I think one of your patients is missing.

01:17.911 --> 01:21.278
-Sasha Woodman, early 203.
-I’m sorry, who?

01:22.082 --> 01:23.322
Has a thing for bees.

01:23.500 --> 01:26.492
We 7/ check out our records, Miss... ?

01:27.087 --> 01:28.497
[PHONE BEEPS OFF]

01:28.672 --> 01:31.505
-I didn't escape.
-Back off.

01:31.675 --> 01:35.167
You or any of your swarm try and sting me
and I will go Black Flag on you.

01:35.345 --> 01:37.427
-Do I know you?
-Chloe Sullivan.

01:38.015 --> 01:42.850
Freshman year, you tried to go queen bee
and kill two of my best friends.

01:43.020 --> 01:44.976
How did you get past the orderlies?

01:45.147 --> 01:47.638
You don't understand,
I don't belong in Belle Reve.

01:47.816 --> 01:49.852
I'm not a meteor freak anymore.

01:50.027 --> 01:52.109
I've been cured.

01:56.074 --> 01:57.689
A few weeks ago...

01:57.868 --> 01:58.948
...I had an operation.

02:00.662 --> 02:02.698
Operation?

02:02.873 --> 02:04.409
Who was the doctor?

02:05.167 --> 02:07.203
Curtis Knox.

02:07.795 --> 02:09.706
He changed my life.

02:10.714 --> 02:14.332
My family told me about the terrible things
I did in the past.

02:14.510 --> 02:16.216
But I'm different now.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.513
What do you mean, your family told you?

02:18.889 --> 02:22.723
When they took away my powers,
some of my memory went along with it.

02:22.893 --> 02:26.351
The last six years are blank.

02:27.815 --> 02:31.774
If I did anything to you or your friends...

02:32.069 --> 02:33.855
...l'm really sorry.

03:02.766 --> 03:04.757
[KEYS JINGLING]

03:08.480 --> 03:09.765
[GASPS]

03:09.940 --> 03:13.774
Ah. Dr. Knox, you scared me.

03:13.944 --> 03:15.104
What are you doing here?

03:17.114 --> 03:19.446
You have something I need.

03:19.783 --> 03:20.772
I do?

03:20.951 --> 03:22.316
[CH UCKLES]

03:22.494 --> 03:23.529
[SCREAMING]

03:24.830 --> 03:26.445
KNOX:
Shh, Shh, shh.

03:26.623 --> 03:28.033
[SCREAMING STOPS]

04:40.405 --> 04:41.440
Mmm.

04:41.615 --> 04:46.234
Bobby Flay, Rachael Ray, look out,
here comes Lana Lang.

04:46.411 --> 04:49.244
-What are you making?
-Clark's favorite, blueberry pancakes.

04:49.414 --> 04:51.996
I wanna surprise him before he wakes up.

04:52.376 --> 04:54.207
This is what I don't get.

04:54.378 --> 04:56.539
You guys are so gaga over each other.

04:57.339 --> 04:59.830
And you've known
each other forever, right?

05:00.050 --> 05:01.540
What took you so long?

05:02.803 --> 05:06.887
Well, as long as Clark kept his secret,
it was impossible.

05:09.059 --> 05:13.723
So is it, like, a human thing
to be so secretive and cautious or what?

05:13.897 --> 05:16.354
No, I think it's just a Clark thing.

05:16.525 --> 05:20.564
But he's only that way because
he cares so much about protecting people.

05:23.907 --> 05:26.819
Lana, you didn't have to do all this.
It looks great.

05:27.411 --> 05:29.117
Yeah, but we're out of maple syrup.

05:34.918 --> 05:37.079
Did you just go to the store?

05:37.879 --> 05:38.914
Vermont's ﬁnest.

05:40.424 --> 05:42.585
What happened to not showing off
your powers?

05:47.681 --> 05:48.966
Stay away from Kal-El.

05:49.141 --> 05:51.632
You might've been able to bully me
on Krypton...

05:51.810 --> 05:53.846
...but not on this planet.

05:56.189 --> 05:58.225
You two know each other?

06:00.944 --> 06:05.313
He's the one that broke into our house
and forced my family from our home.

06:05.490 --> 06:08.357
Considering what your father did,
you were lucky.

06:09.369 --> 06:10.449
What's he doing here?

06:11.830 --> 06:13.445
He's saved my life. He's a friend.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.286
Then picking friends
isn't one of your skills.

06:19.796 --> 06:21.878
Watch your back, Kal-El.

06:27.596 --> 06:30.212
Let me guess,
you're from Krypton as well?

06:34.102 --> 06:36.343
Mars, actually.

06:41.151 --> 06:44.985
Well, I'll let you two catch up.

06:45.155 --> 06:48.647
I'm gonna go
and meet Aunt Nell in Metropolis.

06:50.160 --> 06:52.242
It was nice to meet you.

07:08.011 --> 07:10.969
JOHN: Your cousin's arrival
cannot be taken lightly, Kai-El.

07:12.140 --> 07:14.472
Went to see my father,
he gave me the same warning.

07:14.643 --> 07:17.350
I don't get it. She's my cousin.
The only family I have...

07:17.521 --> 07:20.137
...besides a disembodied voice
from the Arctic.

07:20.315 --> 07:22.601
She could use your longing for family
against you.

07:22.776 --> 07:24.186
She's dangerous.

07:25.695 --> 07:27.606
Her father tried to assassinate Jor-El.

07:29.032 --> 07:30.363
They were brothers.

07:30.534 --> 07:33.526
Their hatred for one another
was stronger than any familial bond.

07:36.706 --> 07:37.957
Does Kara have her crystal?

07:39.751 --> 07:43.335
Not anymore. It was in her ship
when it exploded but now it's missing.

07:43.922 --> 07:48.165
-l've been trying to ﬁnd it, but no luck.
-If she gets to that crystal...

07:48.343 --> 07:51.335
...everything you hold dear in this world
could be lost.

07:51.763 --> 07:54.345
You must ﬁnd the crystal before Kara.

07:55.559 --> 07:58.551
JOHN:
Trust is a luxury you cannot afford.

08:12.742 --> 08:14.733
My apologies for keeping you waiting.

08:16.663 --> 08:21.453
Mussolini once killed a conductor
for not keeping a train on schedule.

08:21.626 --> 08:25.084
Fortunately, I'm inﬁnitely more patient
than ll Duce.

08:25.797 --> 08:28.539
Mussolini went down in defeat, doctor.

08:28.717 --> 08:31.550
I won't accept that
in what we're undertaking.

08:31.720 --> 08:34.837
Well, hiring me
is certainly a winning strategy.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.755
Legions of your own scientists said...

08:36.933 --> 08:39.515
...that curing the meteor-infected
was impossible.

08:39.686 --> 08:45.477
Well, as impressive as your results are,
some of your practices deeply concern me.

08:46.109 --> 08:50.478
l sever the cerebral wiring of the freaks
in your gallery and you pay me my fee.

08:50.655 --> 08:52.520
End of story.

08:52.699 --> 08:56.066
You've authorized batteries of tests
I never approved.

08:56.244 --> 08:59.657
Are the levels of meteor-rock toxicity
in the patients' vital organs...

08:59.831 --> 09:01.787
...really relevant to the task at hand?

09:03.210 --> 09:06.623
Mankind's greatest advances
would never have seen the light of day...

09:06.796 --> 09:12.507
...had the genius minds behind them
been scrutinized under a microscope.

09:13.637 --> 09:15.127
Leave the science to me.

09:16.848 --> 09:20.056
Doctor, three of my patients are missing.

09:21.686 --> 09:24.803
You wouldn't have any idea why someone
with a brand-new lease on life...

09:24.981 --> 09:26.391
...would suddenly disappear?

09:26.566 --> 09:29.979
Perhaps it's because you insisted
on eradicating any recollection...

09:30.153 --> 09:32.815
...of their stay at Hotel 33.1.

09:32.989 --> 09:35.822
No, I insisted they be able
to start new lives...

09:35.992 --> 09:37.983
...unfettered by disturbing memories.

09:38.161 --> 09:40.368
Especially those
that could incriminate you.

09:45.460 --> 09:48.827
If there's nothing else,
I have a schedule to keep.

10:02.185 --> 10:04.176
[BACH'S "CELLO SUITE IN G - PRELUDE"
PLAYING]

10:21.496 --> 10:24.363
KNOX:
I have good news, my love.

10:27.085 --> 10:30.043
I found another piece of the puzzle.

10:51.609 --> 10:53.600
[SASHA GRUNTING]

10:54.863 --> 10:57.980
No. No, no.

10:58.575 --> 10:59.906
Please let me go.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.571
KNOX:
Shh, shh.

11:02.746 --> 11:04.953
Relax, Sasha.

11:05.332 --> 11:07.368
Just relax.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.158
-No.
-You're here...

11:12.255 --> 11:14.792
...to serve a greater purpose.

11:31.858 --> 11:33.974
Is my girl ready to rock?

11:34.277 --> 11:36.393
We either hit Chang's
on the way to the show...

11:36.571 --> 11:38.482
...or chow down chilidogs at the arena.

11:38.656 --> 11:42.240
Jimmy, I know you spent a small fortune
on these tickets tonight but--

11:42.410 --> 11:46.904
Ow. Why is the word "but" never followed
by something good?

11:47.082 --> 11:48.743
Would I be the worst girlfriend...

11:48.917 --> 11:52.626
...if I ask for a rain check
on our night out on the town tonight?

11:53.630 --> 11:55.336
I know. I'll make it up to you.

11:55.507 --> 11:58.590
It's just-- I'm chasing down a hot lead
on the meteor-challenged.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.625
And this can't wait till tomorrow?

12:00.845 --> 12:03.587
Look, please don't take this personally.

12:03.765 --> 12:07.383
I thought I could deal with this but
everything is about meteor freaks lately.

12:07.560 --> 12:10.802
Okay, I thought we agreed that
we weren't gonna use that word anymore.

12:10.980 --> 12:11.969
It's what they are.

12:12.148 --> 12:16.266
If those freaks were locked up in Belle Reve,
maybe I'd get to see you once in a while.

12:23.368 --> 12:25.324
[WHOOSHING]

12:25.829 --> 12:28.366
Can Dr. Curtis Knox take a back seat?
I need your help.

12:28.540 --> 12:32.124
You'll have to hang a bell around your neck
so I can hear when you're coming.

12:32.293 --> 12:35.080
I need you to help me ﬁnd
Kara's missing crystal, all right?

12:35.255 --> 12:38.167
-Check the database, satellite imagery--
-Clark.

12:38.341 --> 12:40.673
You'll have to ﬂy solo,
my dance card's full.

12:41.177 --> 12:43.759
-Chloe, this is important.
-l'm sure that it is.

12:43.930 --> 12:47.297
I know that from Mount Olympus
the view must seem like us mere mortals...

12:47.475 --> 12:50.217
...have nothing better to do
than help you look for crystal.

12:50.395 --> 12:53.182
But believe it or not,
I have important things to do too.

12:54.524 --> 12:56.060
Chloe.

13:08.121 --> 13:09.611
So...

13:09.789 --> 13:12.872
...tell me how I can help you, Miss...

13:13.042 --> 13:14.703
...Sullivan.

13:16.254 --> 13:18.370
I'm a meteor freak...

13:19.257 --> 13:22.875
...and I wanna be cured.

13:29.142 --> 13:31.133
[TYPING]

13:43.823 --> 13:45.438
CLARK:
Lana?

13:46.743 --> 13:48.404
Hey.

13:48.745 --> 13:51.157
Sorry about the Clash of the Titans
this morning.

13:51.331 --> 13:52.662
I'll get used to it.

13:53.124 --> 13:57.458
You're home early. I thought Chloe was
helping you to track down Kara's crystal.

13:58.213 --> 14:00.295
Lana, has she opened up to you
about anything?

14:00.465 --> 14:02.501
Maybe something
that's been bothering her?

14:03.051 --> 14:06.839
No, she's been working 24/7
to impress that wonder-boy editor.

14:07.013 --> 14:09.675
She was researching a story...

14:09.849 --> 14:11.009
...about a Dr. Knox.

14:11.184 --> 14:12.594
Curtis Knox?

14:12.769 --> 14:13.884
You've heard of him?

14:14.062 --> 14:16.599
Yeah, he's a neurosurgeon.

14:16.773 --> 14:19.890
I've heard a rumor that he's working
with meteor-infected people.

14:22.237 --> 14:24.023
How do you know all this?

14:24.572 --> 14:27.564
Well, I've been doing my own research
on the meteor-infected.

14:29.410 --> 14:32.072
More people than just me
have been hurt by Lex...

14:32.247 --> 14:33.953
...and they need help.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.500
And I wanna do whatever I can.

14:36.960 --> 14:38.325
[CH UCKLES]

14:38.503 --> 14:41.461
I didn't know you had a secret plan
to save the world.

14:41.631 --> 14:43.713
So far, I've only made a few contacts.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.124
Knox's name just came up.

14:46.594 --> 14:47.925
As amazing as it sounds...

14:48.096 --> 14:50.929
...he's using brain surgery
to remove their powers.

14:54.227 --> 14:55.683
That actually explains a lot.

14:56.145 --> 14:58.978
A headline like this
could change Chloe's life.

15:01.192 --> 15:02.648
Yeah.

15:09.325 --> 15:13.364
Trust me, if these seats were any closer,
you'd be arrested for stalking the band.

15:13.538 --> 15:17.156
I'm scoring big points
with the boyfriend, Olsen. Ring that bell.

15:19.335 --> 15:20.745
There it is.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.421
KARA:
James.

15:22.589 --> 15:23.704
Hey.

15:23.881 --> 15:25.462
I'm so glad I found you.

15:26.509 --> 15:27.749
Really?

15:27.927 --> 15:32.011
Yeah, I've been looking all over for Lois.
Have you seen her?

15:33.308 --> 15:34.388
You'll need a telescope.

15:34.559 --> 15:38.723
New editor sent her to the City of Angels
to get a quote from the DUI of the week.

15:40.356 --> 15:41.857
Bummer.

15:42.275 --> 15:47.019
I heard that she snuck into a grain silo
and took some videos of a spaceship.

15:47.196 --> 15:49.232
I was kind of hoping
I could sneak a peek.

15:49.407 --> 15:50.692
Bit of an ETjunkie.

15:52.076 --> 15:55.159
No kidding, me too.
I used to sit in the backyard...

15:55.330 --> 15:58.197
...and try and pick up Martian signals
on my dad's ham radio.

15:58.374 --> 16:01.207
Um.... Martians use infrared, silly.

16:02.211 --> 16:03.291
[LAUGHS]

16:03.880 --> 16:05.290
Well—

16:05.465 --> 16:09.049
Unfortunately, Lois' video is nothing
to phone home about.

16:09.260 --> 16:11.842
Tech guy couldn't get anything off it
but static.

16:13.014 --> 16:16.882
Well, you know your way
around cameras, right?

16:17.185 --> 16:20.177
And I bet you're a lot smarter than he is.

16:20.521 --> 16:22.773
Is there anything that you could do?

16:25.902 --> 16:27.312
What the heck?

16:27.487 --> 16:29.773
It's not like I'm doing anything else
tonight.

16:30.281 --> 16:33.318
Yeah, I'll crunch a few pixels,
see what I can come up with.

16:33.493 --> 16:34.778
Great.

16:34.952 --> 16:37.443
You are my hero.

16:37.914 --> 16:41.247
Call my cell when you're done
and I'll be here in a blink.

16:43.294 --> 16:44.750
Thanks.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.173
Uh-huh.

17:00.687 --> 17:03.599
How's the article going about Dr. Knox?

17:06.109 --> 17:10.443
He's doing some interesting research
but I don't believe there's a story there.

17:11.280 --> 17:13.236
Neither do I.

17:14.909 --> 17:16.445
Chloe, you're a good liar.

17:16.619 --> 17:18.985
You've had lots of experience
keeping my secret.

17:19.664 --> 17:22.827
But I don't believe
you're researching Knox for an article.

17:23.000 --> 17:24.831
I think it's about the procedure.

17:28.464 --> 17:30.921
Then you realize that he's my only hope.

17:32.927 --> 17:35.794
Dr. Knox said that he could ﬁt me in
at the end of this week.

17:35.972 --> 17:38.714
Chlo, you don't know anything
about this doctor.

17:38.891 --> 17:42.133
I know that he can give me a chance
at a normal life.

17:42.311 --> 17:46.304
Look, I understand wanting
to have a normal life, I do.

17:46.482 --> 17:49.849
-But brain surgery is not the way to do it.
-You don't understand, Clark.

17:50.027 --> 17:52.154
Going psycho
or turning into a serial killer...

17:52.321 --> 17:54.858
...aren't the only two things
I have to worry about.

17:55.032 --> 17:58.320
When I healed Lois in that dam,
it almost killed me.

17:58.494 --> 18:01.486
Who's to say the next time
I try and save someone isn't my last?

18:03.207 --> 18:05.243
What are the side effects
of the procedure?

18:07.670 --> 18:10.127
-Potentially, memory loss.
-Chloe--

18:10.298 --> 18:13.165
If I have to give up a little of my past
to gain a future, then so be it.

18:13.342 --> 18:17.460
You're gonna forget everything.
You'll forget your friends, your experiences.

18:18.890 --> 18:20.881
You're gonna forget me.

18:21.684 --> 18:23.549
You're gonna forget me.

18:26.647 --> 18:28.057
[CH UCKLES]

18:31.027 --> 18:34.110
People will be there when I come back
to ﬁll in the blanks.

18:34.280 --> 18:36.191
In time, I'll be ﬁne.

18:40.912 --> 18:44.029
Clark, if you wanna save me, let me go.

19:01.057 --> 19:02.593
[GRUNTING]

19:22.829 --> 19:25.616
I applaud your ingenuity, doctor.

19:26.290 --> 19:29.077
After mulching the body
into the fertilizer supply...

19:29.252 --> 19:33.086
...by week's end, her DNA will be spread
over every cornﬁeld in Kansas.

19:33.256 --> 19:35.372
Oh, Lex.

19:35.925 --> 19:39.417
If only you were a typical rich kid
chasing women across the globe...

19:39.595 --> 19:42.837
...instead of dabbling with science
that you don't understand.

19:43.015 --> 19:47.384
You're killing spree stops right now.
I'm not gonna let you hurt one more person.

19:47.562 --> 19:50.725
Countless patients are living new lives...

19:50.898 --> 19:54.732
...with no idea what you did to them,
thanks to me.

19:54.902 --> 19:57.279
How about the ones you murdered?

19:57.446 --> 19:59.482
They're the chosen few.

19:59.657 --> 20:03.320
The reason I created a cure
and came knocking at your door...

20:03.494 --> 20:07.612
...because I knew that somewhere
in your museum of oddities...

20:07.790 --> 20:09.781
...I would ﬁnd the ones I was looking for.

20:09.959 --> 20:10.994
[GUN COCKS]

20:11.168 --> 20:13.295
Your practice is closed, doctor.

20:13.629 --> 20:16.871
You come one step closer
and I swear to God I will shoot you.

20:17.216 --> 20:18.626
[CH UCKLES]

20:19.510 --> 20:21.421
I'm quaking in my boots.

20:22.805 --> 20:24.796
[GRUNTING]

20:39.071 --> 20:40.186
[GRUNTS]

20:40.364 --> 20:42.696
Son of a bitch.

20:49.081 --> 20:53.791
I have been speared by Mayan warriors...

20:54.670 --> 20:57.332
...survived Mongols' arrows...

20:57.506 --> 21:01.670
...and the cold steel
of Crusaders' blades.

21:02.845 --> 21:07.885
What makes you think the sting of a 9 mm
could slow me down?

21:13.856 --> 21:15.187
Aah!

21:40.216 --> 21:41.205
[SIGHS]

21:41.384 --> 21:44.046
So you're no Mr. Miyagi.

21:44.220 --> 21:47.553
But that's okay because...

21:47.723 --> 21:49.634
...I know a little trick.

21:51.435 --> 21:54.893
Now you move the top stick
and keep the lower one straight...

21:55.064 --> 21:58.056
...and you never,
never let the noodles intimidate you.

21:58.234 --> 21:59.770
[CH UCKLES]

21:59.944 --> 22:02.401
Okay, let's do this.

22:05.908 --> 22:07.318
[CH UCKLES]

22:10.913 --> 22:12.323
I knew it. You're a natural.

22:13.791 --> 22:16.032
You're a really patient teacher.

22:16.752 --> 22:18.492
Thanks.

22:20.089 --> 22:21.454
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

22:21.632 --> 22:23.588
COMPUTER:
Render complete.

22:23.759 --> 22:26.136
Video Kodak rendering completed.

22:26.303 --> 22:28.214
That's not the ship.

22:28.389 --> 22:30.380
But we've got something.

22:30.683 --> 22:34.471
Flintlock is a technology supplier
for a security branch of the government.

22:34.645 --> 22:36.260
The government?

22:36.439 --> 22:37.428
[CH UCKLES]

22:37.606 --> 22:40.769
Looks like we got another Area 51
right in the heart of Kansas.

22:40.943 --> 22:42.444
Oh, Chloe's gonna do backﬂips.

22:42.820 --> 22:45.232
No, you can't tell Chloe.

22:45.489 --> 22:47.025
Why not?

22:47.950 --> 22:49.110
Well, she'd tell Clark...

22:49.285 --> 22:52.448
...and he can't stand my obsession
with UFOs.

22:52.621 --> 22:56.785
It's exactly what Chloe needs to stay on
her new editor's honor roll. I gotta tell her.

22:57.960 --> 22:59.621
James...

23:00.129 --> 23:01.414
...I know I can trust you.

23:02.965 --> 23:05.297
This has to be our secret.

23:05.468 --> 23:07.254
Okay, it's between you and me.

23:11.140 --> 23:12.630
Chloe?

23:15.227 --> 23:16.433
You want some Chinese?

23:16.604 --> 23:19.562
It's good
but they really make you work for it.

23:20.691 --> 23:23.649
What are you doing here?
I thought you said you were busy.

23:24.153 --> 23:26.519
And we were just—

23:28.324 --> 23:29.905
Look, I can explain.

23:30.743 --> 23:32.529
There's no need.

23:33.037 --> 23:34.072
I have to go.

23:34.413 --> 23:35.869
Chloe...

23:36.248 --> 23:38.534
...I swear it's not what it looks like.

23:39.335 --> 23:40.996
Bye, Jimmy.

23:49.053 --> 23:50.418
[SIGHS]

23:52.598 --> 23:54.589
[SIREN WAILING]

24:09.365 --> 24:12.482
You're the last person
I thought would save me.

24:13.202 --> 24:17.195
I was following that butcher you used to
erase the memories of your 33.1 victims.

24:18.707 --> 24:22.040
-Lana told you about Dr. Knox, didn't she?
-Don't bring Lana into this.

24:22.211 --> 24:24.793
No point lying for her, Clark.

24:25.005 --> 24:28.543
I know Lana's somehow
been uncovering company secrets...

24:28.717 --> 24:32.335
...probably using the $10 million
she stole from me to do it.

24:32.888 --> 24:35.675
At the moment,
I'd say it's money well spent.

24:35.850 --> 24:38.262
If she hadn't tipped you off,
I'd be in the morgue.

24:38.435 --> 24:40.812
You're just as guilty as that doctor.

24:41.438 --> 24:44.896
Makes me sick to think
that I had to take a life for yours.

24:46.193 --> 24:47.979
Knox isn't dead, Clark.

24:53.117 --> 24:55.403
He came after me.

24:55.995 --> 24:59.237
I put six bullets in his chest.

24:59.915 --> 25:02.201
They didn't leave a scratch.

25:04.211 --> 25:06.202
You're saying Knox is still alive?

25:06.380 --> 25:10.589
Not only is he alive,
he's murdering his patients one by one.

25:17.641 --> 25:19.927
Miss Sullivan, right on time.

25:20.269 --> 25:21.975
Thank you for coming on short notice.

25:22.146 --> 25:25.855
I'm just glad my test results
proved I could have the procedure.

25:26.025 --> 25:27.060
You're one of a kind.

25:27.234 --> 25:31.443
The level of meteor-rock concentration
in your heart is extraordinary.

25:33.490 --> 25:35.105
In my heart?

25:35.284 --> 25:39.152
Just relax, after tonight,
you'll have nothing to worry about.

25:44.335 --> 25:46.792
Where are all your staff?

25:47.713 --> 25:49.419
They'll be here shortly.

25:55.721 --> 25:56.756
What is that?

25:59.433 --> 26:01.424
[CHLOE GRUNTING]

26:04.438 --> 26:06.144
No, no, no.

26:06.565 --> 26:07.645
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

26:07.816 --> 26:09.807
KNOX:
Shh, Shh, shh.

26:22.665 --> 26:23.825
Jimmy.

26:23.999 --> 26:26.160
Where's Chloe?
I've been looking everywhere.

26:26.335 --> 26:29.577
We had a major misunderstanding, C.K.

26:30.005 --> 26:31.666
-I need your help.
-There's no time.

26:31.840 --> 26:32.966
Where is she?

26:34.343 --> 26:37.255
She's jumping to conclusions,
stormed out before I'd explain.

26:37.429 --> 26:39.215
-Did she say where she was going?
-No.

26:39.390 --> 26:43.099
She dropped off this Rubik's cube of a rant.
I have no idea what it means.

26:43.269 --> 26:47.478
"I might not remember you, so don't let me
forget why we belong together."

26:48.482 --> 26:51.315
I don't get it.
C.K., what's happening tonight?

26:54.071 --> 26:56.062
[GRUNTING]

27:01.412 --> 27:02.447
What are you doing?

27:03.872 --> 27:08.206
Taking your heart and giving it to Sophia.

27:11.505 --> 27:14.338
Thanks to you, Chloe Sullivan...

27:15.342 --> 27:17.298
...my love will last forever.

27:31.567 --> 27:32.852
Where did Knox take Chloe?

27:33.360 --> 27:36.102
Look, Clark, I wanna stop Knox
as much as you do.

27:36.280 --> 27:38.191
I've checked every address
we had on ﬁle.

27:38.365 --> 27:40.651
-They're dead ends.
-He didn't disappear into thin air.

27:40.826 --> 27:43.317
No, but he's had a lot of experience
covering his tracks.

27:43.495 --> 27:44.905
[PHONE BEEPS]

27:45.080 --> 27:46.695
Send me the pictures on Knox.

27:47.791 --> 27:51.500
I used face-recognition software
to run an image search.

27:51.920 --> 27:53.535
Here we go.

27:55.674 --> 27:57.960
Knox wasn't alive
during World War II, Lex.

27:58.135 --> 28:01.423
-He's too young.
-He's much older than he looks.

28:01.805 --> 28:04.512
This is Knox in 1888.

28:05.100 --> 28:06.931
And here he is in 1675.

28:08.937 --> 28:12.680
Clark, he's had a thousand names
and he's lived for centuries.

28:12.858 --> 28:14.769
That's why you can't kill him.

28:14.943 --> 28:16.604
Curtis Knox is immortal.

28:19.198 --> 28:21.780
He couldn't have gotten far.
He must've dropped this...

28:21.950 --> 28:24.987
...in the struggle with Chloe.
It stopped less than an hour ago.

28:27.122 --> 28:29.454
[LEX READS INSCRIPTION]

28:29.625 --> 28:33.584
"May you live forever."
It's a Roman greeting. I've seen this before.

28:35.214 --> 28:36.750
The Victorian Arms?

28:37.466 --> 28:40.583
Knox was the robber baron who owned it.
He lived there in the '20s.

28:42.638 --> 28:44.629
Maybe he never moved.

28:47.309 --> 28:50.426
If your wife is sick,
I can cure her with my abilities.

28:50.604 --> 28:52.686
Sophia is perfectly healthy.

28:52.856 --> 28:57.190
I've induced her coma simply
to reduce her stress before the procedure.

28:57.361 --> 29:00.273
You put her in a coma
because you knew that she would freak...

29:00.447 --> 29:04.156
...if she knew you were playing fatal games
of Operation with innocent people.

29:04.326 --> 29:06.738
That doesn't sound like
eternal love to me.

29:07.496 --> 29:09.327
You've been around, what...

29:09.790 --> 29:11.655
...two decades?

29:12.793 --> 29:14.499
What do you know about true love?

29:15.921 --> 29:18.663
I know there's someone
that I wanna live to see again.

29:18.841 --> 29:20.797
A schoolgirl crush.

29:21.343 --> 29:23.174
Very quaint.

29:23.679 --> 29:26.671
Unfortunately,
you won't be able to say goodbye.

29:29.268 --> 29:32.180
Now, let us begin.

29:33.105 --> 29:38.020
I came here for help, not to be cut open
by some Jack the Ripper wannabe.

29:44.992 --> 29:46.948
[CHLOE SCREAMING]

29:49.538 --> 29:50.618
Chloe.

29:54.084 --> 29:55.870
[CLARK GRUNTS]

29:58.380 --> 30:00.792
-Clark.
-Your powers might be far beyond...

30:00.966 --> 30:02.706
...those of mortal men.

30:02.885 --> 30:04.216
You've met your match.

30:04.470 --> 30:05.550
[BOTH GRUNTING]

30:06.555 --> 30:08.045
I won't let you kill anyone else.

30:08.223 --> 30:10.680
I'd kill a thousand more
to never have to be alone.

30:16.190 --> 30:18.806
You don't know the pain
of living centuries...

30:18.984 --> 30:21.691
...watching the women you love
grow old and turn to dust.

30:23.655 --> 30:25.691
You and I are more alike than you think.

30:30.162 --> 30:32.244
I won't go through it again.

30:45.761 --> 30:48.468
Oh, God, what have I done?

30:49.097 --> 30:50.928
Oh, no, no.

30:51.683 --> 30:53.184
No.

30:54.228 --> 30:55.889
My darling.

30:56.063 --> 30:57.678
[GLASSES CLINKING]

31:03.820 --> 31:05.902
[G ROANS]

31:14.790 --> 31:16.200
Oh....

31:18.377 --> 31:20.538
Please don't leave me.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.416
Please.

31:29.471 --> 31:31.462
[CRYING]

32:07.384 --> 32:09.375
[WHOOSHING]

32:13.265 --> 32:14.345
What'd you do with Knox?

32:16.602 --> 32:19.344
Your father and I
had a "don't ask, don't tell" policy...

32:19.521 --> 32:21.762
...when it came to
crime and punishment.

32:22.065 --> 32:24.317
I suggest we abide by the same rules.

32:28.530 --> 32:30.066
You didn't kill him, did you?

32:30.240 --> 32:32.196
Knox is immortal, Kal-El.

32:32.367 --> 32:34.073
You can't kill him.

32:35.287 --> 32:38.370
I know what it's like to have feelings
for the people here.

32:38.874 --> 32:41.536
But the truth is, you'll outlive them all.

32:42.169 --> 32:43.705
And when they're gone...

32:43.879 --> 32:46.495
...you still have a greater calling to fulﬁll.

32:47.090 --> 32:49.001
Have you found the crystal?

32:49.176 --> 32:51.462
I got a little sidetracked.

32:52.304 --> 32:54.966
KARA:
What is Red Eye still doing here?

32:55.223 --> 32:57.384
I heard what he said about my father.

32:58.769 --> 33:01.556
He's the one who can't be trusted.

33:03.523 --> 33:06.265
Ask him to tell you about
what he did to my family.

33:07.027 --> 33:08.733
Your father was a traitor.

33:10.739 --> 33:11.819
He's lying.

33:16.411 --> 33:18.572
Who are you gonna believe, Clark?

33:19.414 --> 33:21.245
Your family...

33:23.210 --> 33:24.996
...or this Martian Manhunter?

33:29.549 --> 33:32.586
Guess this family reunion is over.

33:48.944 --> 33:51.481
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

33:57.953 --> 33:59.284
Hey.

33:59.454 --> 34:04.118
I heard the police shut BCE Clinic down
and that Curtis Knox went AWOL.

34:04.292 --> 34:07.079
Did you have anything to do with that?

34:07.254 --> 34:09.666
Turns out he was killing his patients...

34:11.216 --> 34:13.753
...and Chloe's story got her in
a little over her head.

34:13.927 --> 34:15.963
Oh, my God, is she okay?

34:16.638 --> 34:19.254
You know Chloe,
there's not a lot that can keep her down.

34:19.433 --> 34:22.140
She's lucky to have someone like you
in her life, Clark.

34:22.310 --> 34:23.561
We all are.

34:33.572 --> 34:35.358
What's wrong?

34:38.493 --> 34:39.903
Lex helped me ﬁnd Knox.

34:41.872 --> 34:44.158
Well, he probably has an ulterior motive.

34:44.332 --> 34:48.120
Lex doesn't generally do things
out of the kindness of his heart.

34:50.630 --> 34:53.918
He told me you stole $10 million
from him.

35:01.391 --> 35:03.473
You can see what he's doing, right?

35:03.643 --> 35:06.931
He's trying to destroy what we have
all over again.

35:09.191 --> 35:12.479
Clark, that money was a part
of the divorce settlement.

35:12.652 --> 35:15.189
I plan on using it
to help the meteor-infected people...

35:15.363 --> 35:18.025
...who've been victimized by LuthorCorp.

35:21.578 --> 35:24.786
Don't let Lex's lies come between us.

35:28.919 --> 35:31.877
I would never hide anything from you.

35:56.029 --> 35:58.020
[DEVICE BEEPING]

36:52.085 --> 36:53.450
Hey.

36:55.672 --> 36:57.333
Well, there you are.

37:00.135 --> 37:02.296
Heh. Remember me?

37:02.637 --> 37:04.969
Heh. Jimmy.

37:05.265 --> 37:07.051
That's a good sign.

37:08.643 --> 37:13.137
Your letter was a little Da Vinci Code
and I'm no cryptologist...

37:13.648 --> 37:15.639
...but I brought this...

37:17.694 --> 37:19.730
...to remind you why we belong together.

37:33.543 --> 37:34.953
Oh....

37:35.128 --> 37:39.167
It's the cocktail napkin from that July 4th
party where you gave me your number.

37:39.841 --> 37:42.833
Oh, the Granville Carnival.
This was the best ﬁrst date ever.

37:45.180 --> 37:46.920
And my favorite.

37:47.766 --> 37:50.303
A piece of stained glass
from the bullpen that broke...

37:50.477 --> 37:52.718
...during that weird earthquake last fall.

37:54.105 --> 37:56.847
Okay, now I'm the one
that needs the decoder ring.

37:57.275 --> 37:58.731
Um....

38:00.195 --> 38:03.062
We lost touch for the longest time...

38:03.531 --> 38:06.989
...and the day that we bumped
into each other again, the world...

38:09.704 --> 38:11.535
...well, it literally shook.

38:15.043 --> 38:17.830
And if that's not a sign,
I don't know what is.

38:19.714 --> 38:22.672
Jimmy, I'm so sorry about all the craziness
I put you through...

38:22.842 --> 38:24.798
...in the last couple of weeks.

38:25.512 --> 38:28.549
Well, let's just agree that the future
will be more normal.

38:29.307 --> 38:30.717
Deal?

38:33.770 --> 38:38.230
You know, I don't think
I can make you that promise.

38:40.193 --> 38:44.687
I don't think things will ever be normal
between the two of us.

38:48.410 --> 38:50.275
[INHALES]

38:53.540 --> 38:55.076
Okay.

39:03.258 --> 39:04.919
Wait a sec.

39:06.261 --> 39:07.717
Is this because of Kara?

39:10.890 --> 39:15.259
Because after all the times that you left me
on hold to go run off and help Clark...

39:15.437 --> 39:19.146
...l'd hate to think that you're gonna
give me a hard time for helping Kara once.

39:19.315 --> 39:23.479
No, this isn't about Kara.
This is about me. This is entirely me.

39:27.866 --> 39:29.276
What's going on, Chloe?

39:39.878 --> 39:42.415
If you can't say it...

39:43.048 --> 39:45.960
...heh, try some sign language
or subtitles.

39:49.387 --> 39:50.627
I can't.

39:50.805 --> 39:52.420
I'm
sorry

39:54.142 --> 39:55.598
So am I.

39:57.270 --> 39:59.477
Because I've tried really...

39:59.647 --> 40:02.935
...really hard to be
the understanding boyfriend...

40:03.485 --> 40:07.148
...but there's only so much a guy can take
before there's nothing else to do but jump.

40:10.325 --> 40:11.986
I don't know what to say.

40:14.537 --> 40:17.153
Maybe that earthquake wasn't a sign.

40:21.336 --> 40:24.453
Maybe it was a giant ﬂuke,
just like this relationship.

40:29.260 --> 40:31.000
Maybe you're right.

40:41.022 --> 40:42.558
You know what?

40:47.862 --> 40:50.239
I can't do this anymore, Chloe.

40:54.702 --> 40:56.488
I can't.

41:22.730 --> 41:25.062
Christopher Reeve
changed the world of paralysis...

41:25.233 --> 41:27.895
...proving that one person
really could make a difference.

41:28.069 --> 41:30.401
Today, the Christopher
and Dana Reeve Foundation...

41:30.572 --> 41:33.905
...carries on his mission to ﬁnd cures
and treatments for paralysis...

41:34.075 --> 41:37.283
...that better the health and quality of life
for the community.

41:37.453 --> 41:40.945
But the foundation needs help
to continue its vital work.

41:41.124 --> 41:45.618
By visiting christopherreeve.org
and purchasing a pair of Superman Tags...

41:45.795 --> 41:49.583
...you, too, could be one person
making a difference.

42:15.450 --> 42:17.441
[ENGLISH SDH]
